<h1 class="history-txt">BJP Lime-Lighting And Recontruction Of The Ram Mandir</h1>
<hr>
<h3 class="history-content"> January 2022, the construction of the Ram Mandir in Ayodhya, India, was underway, and the Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP) was actively involved in the process. The Ram Mandir issue has been a significant political and social matter in India for many years.

    The construction of the Ram Mandir gained momentum after the Supreme Court of India's verdict in November 2019, which ruled in favor of building a Hindu temple at the disputed site in Ayodhya. The court also directed the allocation of an alternative piece of land for the construction of a mosque.
    
    The BJP, which has historical roots in the Rashtriya Swayamsevak Sangh (RSS) and other affiliated organizations, has consistently advocated for the construction of the Ram Mandir. The party's involvement in the temple's reconstruction is part of its commitment to fulfilling its ideological and cultural agenda.
    
    The construction project is overseen by the Shri Ram Janmabhoomi Teerth Kshetra, a trust established by the government to facilitate and manage the construction of the temple. The BJP, being the ruling party at the national level, has been actively supporting and promoting the construction efforts.
    
    The development and reconstruction of the Ram Mandir have been significant events that have stirred both political and social discussions in India.</h3>
